# CLIP ChangeLog for x11-apps/xinit

*xinit-1.3.1-r20 (21 Apr 2015)

  21 Apr 2015; Tony Cheneau <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.3.1-r20.ebuild, -xinit-1.3.1-r19.ebuild,
  files/CLIP.livecd:
  Add new "autoinst" kernel boot parameter that starts clip-autoinst (if
  present) when booting livecd (GUI mode only).

*xinit-1.3.1-r19 (26 Feb 2015)

  26 Feb 2015; ANSSI <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.3.1-r19.ebuild, -xinit-1.3.1-r18.ebuild,
  files/CLIP:
  Fixing issue in CLIP session file related to smartcards.
 
*xinit-1.3.1-r18 (26 Feb 2015)

  26 Feb 2015; ANSSI <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.3.1-r18.ebuild, -xinit-1.3.1-r17.ebuild,
  files/CLIP:
  Insert smartcard listing snapshot at login if user is authentified
  by smartcard.
 
*xinit-1.3.1-r17 (11 Jul 2014)

  11 Jul 2014; Tony Cheneau <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.3.1-r17.ebuild, -xinit-1.3.1-r16.ebuild,
  files/CLIP:
  Change the place where the x11 session applications configuration is
  stored in order to make sure it is not user writable. The directory is now
  /etc/conf.d/session and is read-only. Configuration is temporarily written in
  /tmp/session.
  Hotfix for a bug that prevented adeskbar return code from being passed up the
  stack (and thus prevented the halt/reboot commands from working correctly).

*xinit-1.3.1-r16 (10 Jul 2014)

  10 Jul 2014; Tony Cheneau <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.3.1-r16.ebuild, -xinit-1.3.1-r15.ebuild,
  files/CLIP:
  Add support of Openbox theme customization through the /etc/admin/x11/openbox
  configuration file (when it exists). It uses this information (only colors for
  the moment) to fill configuration skeleton that will output the "real" theme
  file in the USER home.
  Improve the robustness of the adeskbar customization (check if the skeleton
  file exists for the corresponding user profile).

*xinit-1.3.1-r15 (27 Jun 2014)

  27 Jun 2014; Tony Cheneau <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.3.1-r15.ebuild, -xinit-1.3.1-r14.ebuild,
  files/CLIP:
  Add support for adeskbar customization through the /etc/admin/x11/adeskbar
  configuration file (if it exists). It uses this information to fill a
  configuration skeleton. When the configuration file is missing, it falls back
  to the existing "hardcoded" configuration file.

*xinit-1.3.1-r14 (05 May 2014)

  05 May 2014; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.3.1-r14.ebuild, -xinit-1.3.1-r13.ebuild,
  files/CLIP:
  Wait 3 seconds before running lxkeymap --autostart in the
  background, to avoid a (presumed) race condition.

*xinit-1.3.1-r13 (21 Feb 2014)

  21 Feb 2014; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
