*xinit-1.0.8-r10 (05 Feb 2010)

  05 Feb 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.0.8-r10.ebuild, -xinit-1.0.8-r9.ebuild,
  files/CLIP:
  Use new 'maximize/minimize' and 'autostart' features of 
  fbpanel-4.12-r46 to simplify the fullscreen session - 
  we now exec fbpanel() itself, with the 'default' profile, 
  just like in non-fullscreen mode, instead of running 
  fbpanel with the 'button' profile, and then exec-ing 
  rm_X_session.sh. The main benefit, beyond simplification,
  is that the 'quit' actions (quit, reboot, halt) in fbpanel
  menu now behave as expected in fullscreen mode. Add to that
  the fact that we no longer have to re-run fbpanel on each
  maximize / minimize...

*xinit-1.0.8-r9 (31 Jan 2010)

  31 Jan 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xinit-1.0.8-r9.ebuild, -xinit-1.0.8-r8.ebuild,
  +files/CLIP, -files/CLIP.1, -files/CLIP.2.pp,
  -files/CLIP-single:
  Remove clip-hermes preprocessing, use a generic "CLIP" session
  that adapts automatically to fullscreen / non-fullscreen cases,
  based on the presence of /var/run/fullscreen and /var/run/has_jail*.
  Also make use of new simplified openbox rc files and fbpanel profiles.

